    <item>
      <title>Building a Serverless Search Engine on AWS with OpenSearch</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/ckloud-journal/posts/opensearch-search-engine/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 10:00:00 -0700</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/ckloud-journal/posts/opensearch-search-engine/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;What I Built&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;what-i-built&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#what-i-built&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The goal was simple but ambitious: build a personal search engine (nicknamed &amp;ldquo;MyGoogle&amp;rdquo;) that lets you upload PDF documents and search their contents through a REST API. The entire pipeline is serverless — from document ingestion to full-text search.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s the workflow at a high level:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Document Ingestion:&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;User uploads PDF → S3 Bucket → Lambda extracts text → Lambda indexes content → OpenSearch&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:1313/ckloud-journal/posts/opensearch-search-engine/feature-architecture.png" />
    </item>
    
